<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">

<A NAME="PLOW-20151231X10K_HTM_PARTI_962301">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	I
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Forward Looking Statements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	This Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;K contains &#x201C;forward
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;looking statements&#x201D; made within the meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. Words such as &#x201C;anticipate,&#x201D; &#x201C;believe,&#x201D; &#x201C;intend,&#x201D; &#x201C;estimate,&#x201D; &#x201C;expect,&#x201D; &#x201C;continue,&#x201D; &#x201C;should,&#x201D; &#x201C;could,&#x201D; &#x201C;may,&#x201D; &#x201C;plan,&#x201D; &#x201C;project,&#x201D; &#x201C;predict,&#x201D; &#x201C;will&#x201D; and similar expressions are intended to identify forward
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209; looking statements. In addition, statements covering our future sales or financial performance and our plans, performance and other objectives, expectations or intentions are forward
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;looking statements, such as statements regarding our liquidity, debt, planned capital expenditures, and adequacy of capital resources and reserves. Factors that could cause our actual results to differ materially from those expressed or implied in such forward

	&#8209;looking statements include, but are not limited to:

<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item&nbsp;
</FONT>
<A NAME="PLOW-20151231X10K_HTM_ITEM1_966608">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1.&nbsp;&nbsp;Business
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	Home to the best selling
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	brands in the industry, Douglas Dynamics, Inc.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(the &#x201C;Company,&#x201D; &#x201C;we,&#x201D; &#x201C;us,&#x201D; &#x201C;our&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	is North America's premier manufacturer of vehicle attachments and equipment. For more than 65 years, the Company has been innovating products that enable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	end users
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	to perform their jobs more efficiently and effectively,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	providing opportunities for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	businesses to increase profitability. Our commitment to continuous improvement enables us to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	consistently produce high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	quality products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	and drive shareholder value. The Douglas Dynamics portfolio includes snow and ice management attachments sold under the BLIZZARD
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	, FISHER
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	, SNOWEX
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	and WESTERN
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	brands, turf care equipment under the TURFEX
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	brand, and industrial maintenance equipment under the SWEEPEX
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	brand.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On December 31, 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, we completed our acquisition of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Henderson by merging a wholly-owned subsidiary of the Company with and into Henderson pursuant to a merger agreement. The acquisition provides the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Company with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Henderson&#x2019;s diverse product portfolio including ice control equipment, snow plows, dump bodies, muni-bodies, and replacement parts.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as a result of the Henderson acquisition, the Company acquired
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Henderson&#x2019;s brands, and access to Henderson&#x2019;s network of authorized dealers. We operate as a single segment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We offer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	broad product line of snowplows and sand and salt spreaders for light trucks
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	that we believe to be the most complete line offered
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in the U.S. and Canadian markets. We also provide a full range of related parts and accessories, which generates an ancillary revenue stream throughout the lifecycle of our snow and ice control equipment.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As a result of the acquisition of Henderson, we also
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	provide customized turnkey solutions to governmental agencies such as Departments of Transportation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(&#x201C;DOTs&#x201D;) and municipalities.&nbsp;&nbsp;We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	also believe that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	wit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	h the addition of Henderson,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	we are now the market leader in the heavy-duty segm
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ent of the North American snow and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ice control market which includes equipment for class 7 and class 8 truck chassis.&nbsp;&nbsp;For the years ended December&nbsp;31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	%, 84
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% and 8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% of our net sales were generated from sales of snow and ice control equipment, respectively, and 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	%, 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% and 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% of our net sales were generated from sales of parts and accessories, respectively.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;While we measure sales of parts and accessories separately from snow and ice control equipment, they are integrated with one another
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	are not separable.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We sell our products through a distributor network primarily to professional snowplowers who are contracted to remove snow and ice from commercial, municipal and residential areas. Over the last 50&nbsp;years, we have engendered exceptional
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	customer loyalty for our products because of our ability to satisfy the stringent demands of our customers for a high degree of quality, reliability and service. As a result, we believe our installed base is the largest in the light truck
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	market with over 500,000 snowplows
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and sand and salt spreaders in service. Because sales of snowplows and sand and salt spreaders are primarily driven by the need of our core end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;user base to replace worn existing equipment, we believe our substantial installed base provides us with a high degree of predictable sales over any extended period of time.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe we have the industry&#x2019;s most extensive distribution network worldwi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	de, which consists of over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2,1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	00 points
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of sale.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	we have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	added Henderson&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	six
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	truck equipment installation facilities located throughout the United States.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Direct points of shipment are predominantly through North American truck equipment and lawn care equipment distributors. Most of our distributors are located throughout the snow belt regions in North America (primarily the Midwest, East and Northeast regions of the United States as well as all provinces of Canada). We have longstanding relationships with many of our distributors. We continually seek to grow and optimize our network by opportunistically adding high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality, well
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;capitalized distributors in select geographic areas and by cross
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;selling our industry
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;leading brands within our distribution network.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Beginning in 2005, we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	have extended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	our reach to international markets, establishing distribution relationships in Northern Europe and Asia, where we believe meaningful growth opportunities exist.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe we are the industry&#x2019;s most operationally efficient manufacturer due to our vertical integration, highly variable cost structure and intense focus on lean manufacturing. We continually seek to use lean principles to reduce costs and increase the efficiency of our manufacturing operations.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	During the year ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	we ma
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	nufactured our products in four
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	facilities that we own in Milwaukee, Wisconsin, Rockland, Maine, Madison Heights, Michigan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and Manchester, Iowa
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Furthermore, our manufacturing efficiency allows us to deliver desired products quickly to our customers during times of sudden and unpredictable snowfall events when our customers need our products immediately.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage5"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#PLOW-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Our Industry
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Both t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	he light truck
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and heavy duty
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	snow an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	d ice control equipment industries in North America consist
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	predominantly of domestic participants that manufacture their products in North America. The annual demand for snow and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ice control equipment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is driven primarily by the replacement cycle of the existing installed base, which is predominantly a function of the average life of a snowplow or spreader and is driven by usage and maintenance practices of the end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;user. We believe actively
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;used snowplows are typically replaced, on average, every 9 to 12&nbsp;years.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe that both light and heavy duty snow and ice control equipment are both driven primarily by the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	replacement cycle of the existing installed base, which is predominantly a function of the average life of a snowplow or spreader and is driven by usage and maintenance practices of the end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;user.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;However, we believe that demand for heavy duty trucks is les
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s elastic than light trucks.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Heavy duty truck end users typically are comprised of local governments and municipalities which plan for and execute planned replacement of equipment over time.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The primary factor influencing the replacement cycle for snow and ice control equipment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for light trucks
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is the level, timing and location of snowfall. Sales of snow and ice control equipment in any given year and region are most heavily influenced by local snowfall levels in the prior snow season. Heavy snowfall during a given winter causes equipment usage to increase, resulting in greater wear and tear and shortened life cycles, thereby creating a need for replacement equipment and additional parts and accessories.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	While snowfall levels vary within a given year and from year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year, snowfall, and the corresponding replacement cycle of snow and ice control equipment, is relatively consistent over multi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year periods. The following chart depicts aggregate annual and ten
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year (based on the typical life of our snowplows) rolling average of the aggregate snowfall levels in 66 cities in 26 snow belt states across the Northeast, East, Midwest and Western United States where we monitor snowfall levels from 1980 to 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. As the chart indicates, since 1984 aggregate snowfall levels in any given rolling ten
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year period have been fairly consistent, ranging
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	from 2,7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2 to 3,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	345
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	inches
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">

	&nbsp;

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/03/09/0001558370-16-003908_PLOW20151231X10K002.JPG" STYLE="WIDTH: 6.72IN; HEIGHT: 4.87IN" ALT="PICTURE 2">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV>
<HR STYLE="BORDER-WIDTH:0;WIDTH:25%;HEIGHT:1PT;COLOR:BLACK;BACKGROUND-COLOR:BLACK;" ALIGN="LEFT">
</HR>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Note:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 21PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The 10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year rolling average snowfall is not presented prior to 1984 for purposes of the calculation due to lack of snowfall data prior to 1975. Snowfall data in this chart is not adjusted for snowfall outside of the 66 cities in the 26 states reflected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Source:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 15PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration&#x2019;s National Weather Service.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The demand for snow and ice control equipment can also be influenced by general economic conditions in the United States, as well as local economic conditions in the snow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;belt regions in North America. In stronger economic conditions, our end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users may choose to replace or upgrade existing equipment before its useful life has ended, while in weak economic conditions, our end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users may seek to extend the useful life of equipment, thereby increasing the sales of parts and accessories. However, since snow and ice control management is a non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;discretionary service necessary to ensure public safety and continued personal and commercial mobility in populated areas that receive snowfall, end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users cannot extend the useful life of snow and ice control equipment indefinitely and must replace equipment that has become too worn, unsafe or unreliable, regardless of economic conditions. While our parts and accessories yield slightly higher gross margins than our snow and ice control equipment, they yield significantly lower revenue than equipment sales, which adversely affects our results of operations.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Sales of parts and accessories for 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	were approximately 74
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% higher than average annual parts and accessories sales over the preceding ten years.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Of the increase, 24%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	was attributable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to parts and accessory sales of Henderson
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	remaining
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	higher than average parts and accessories sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	can be primarily
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	attributed to the timing, location and amount of the snowfall for the six
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;month snow season ended March&nbsp;31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	See
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>

	6

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#PLOW-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">

</FONT>

</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201C;Management&#x2019;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations&#x2014;Seasonality and Year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;Year Variability.&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;term growth in the overall snow and ice control equipment market also results from geographic expansion of developed areas in the snow belt regions of North America, as well as consumer demand for technological enhancements in snow and ice control equipment and related parts and accessories that improves efficiency and reliability. Continued construction in the snow belt regions in North America increases the aggregate area requiring snow and ice removal, thereby growing the market for snow and ice control equipment. In addition, the development and sale of more reliable, more efficient and more sophisticated products have contributed to an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	approximate 2% to 4% average
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	unit price increase in each of the past five years.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Our Competitive Strengths
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We compete solely with other North American manufacturers who do not benefit from our extensive distributor network, manufacturing efficiencies and depth and breadth of products. As the market leader in snow and ice control equipment for light trucks and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	following the Henderson acquisition,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	heavy duty trucks, we enjoy a set of competitive advantages versus smaller equipment providers, which allows us to generate robust cash flows in all snowfall environments and to support continued investment in our products, distribution capabilities and brand regardless of annual volume fluctuations. We believe these advantages are rooted in the following competitive strengths and reinforces our industry leadership over time.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Exceptional Customer Loyalty and Brand Equity.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;Our brands enjoy exceptional customer loyalty and brand equity in the snow and ice control equipment industry with both end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users and distributors, which have been developed through over 50&nbsp;years of superior innovation, productivity, reliability and support, consistently delivered season after season. We believe past brand experience, rather than price, is the key factor impacting snowplow purchasing decisions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Broadest and Most Innovative Product Offering.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;We provide the industry&#x2019;s broadest product offering with a full range of snowplows, sand and salt spreaders and related parts and accessories. We believe we maintain the industry&#x2019;s largest and most advanced in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;house new product development program, historically introducing several new and redesigned products each year. Our broad product offering and commitment to new product development is essential to maintaining and growing our leading market share position as well as continuing to increase the profitability of our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Extensive North American Distributor Network.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;With
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	over 2,1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	00 points of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sale, we benefit from having
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	what we believe to be
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the most extensive distributor network in the industry, providing a significant competitive advantage over our peers. Our distributors function not only as sales and support agents (providing access to parts and service), but also as industry partners providing real
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;time end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;user information, such as retail inventory levels, changing consumer preferences or desired functionality enhancements, which we use as the basis for our product development efforts.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Leader in Operational Efficiency.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;We believe we are a leader in operational efficiency in our industry, resulting from our application of lean manufacturing principles and a highly variable cost structure. By utilizing lean principles, we are able to adjust production levels easily to meet fluctuating demand, while controlling costs in slower periods. This operational efficiency is supplemented by our highly variable cost structure, driven in part by our access to a sizable temporary workforce (comprising approximately 10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;15% of our total workforce during average snowfall years), which we can quickly adjust, as needed. These manufacturing efficiencies enable us to respond rapidly to urgent customer demand during times of sudden and unpredictable snowfalls, allowing us to provide exceptional service to our existing customer base and capture new customers from competitors that we believe cannot service their customers&#x2019; needs with the same speed and reliability.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Strong Cash Flow Generation.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;We are able to generate significant cash flow as a result of relatively consistent high profitability, low capital spending requirements and predictable timing of our working capital requirements. Our cash flow results will also benefit substantially from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	approximately $19.0&nbsp;million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of annual tax
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;deductible intangible and goo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	dwill expense over the next three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years, which has the impact of reducing our corporate taxes owed by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	approximately $7.3&nbsp;million on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	an annual basis during this period, in the event we have sufficient taxable income to utilize such benefit. Our significant cash flow has allowed us to reinvest in our business, pay down long term debt, and pay substantial dividends on a pro rata basis to our stockholders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Experienced Management Team.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;We believe our business benefits from an exceptional management team that is responsible for establishing our leadership in the snow and ice control equipment industry for light trucks. Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	senior management team, consisting of four officers,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	has an average of approximately 25
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;years of weather
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;related industry experience and an average of over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	fifteen
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years with our company. James Janik, our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Chairman,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	President and Chief Executive Offic
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	er, has been with us for over 23
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;years and in his
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	role
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	as President and Chief Executive Officer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	since 2000, and through his strategic vision, we have been able to expand our distributor network and grow our market leading position.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Our Business Strategy
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our business strategy is to capitalize on our competitive strengths to maximize cash flow to pay dividends, reduce indebtedness and reinvest in our business to create stockholder value.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have also developed a management system called the Douglas Dynamics Management System that is intended to assist in value creation and enhanced customer service.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The building blocks of our strategy are:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Continuous Product Innovation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;We believe new product innovation is critical to maintaining and growing our market
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;leading position in the snow and ice control equipment industry. We will continue to focus on developing innovative solutions to increase productivity, ease of use, reliability, durability and serviceability of our products and on incorporating lean manufacturing concepts into our product development process, which has allowed us to reduce the overall cost of development and, more importantly, to reduce our time
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;market by nearly one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;half.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Distributor Network Optimization.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;We will continually seek opportunities to continue to expand our extensive distribution network by adding high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	quality, well
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;capitalized distributors in select geographic areas and by cross
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;selling our industry
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;leading brands within our distribution network to ensure we maximize our ability to generate revenue while protecting our industry leading reputation, customer loyalty and brands. We will also focus on optimizing this network by providing in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;depth training, valuable distributor support and attractive promotional and incentive opportunities. As a result of these efforts, we believe a majority of our distributors choose to sell our products exclusively. We believe this sizable high quality network is unique in the industry, providing us with valuable insight into purchasing trends and customer preferences, and would be very difficult to replicate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Aggressive Asset Management and Profit Focus.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;We will continue to aggressively manage our assets in order to maximize our cash flow generation despite seasonal and annual variability in snowfall levels. We believe our ability is unique in our industry and enables us to achieve attractive margins in all snowfall environments. Key elements of our asset management and profit focus strategies include:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	employment of a highly variable cost structure, which allows us to quickly adjust costs in response to real
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;time changes in demand;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	use of enterprise
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;wide lean principles, which allow us to easily adjust production levels up or down to meet demand;
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>

</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	implementation of a pre
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;season order program, which incentivizes distributors to place orders prior to the retail selling season and thereby enables us to more efficiently utilize our assets; and
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	development of a vertically integrated business model, which we believe provides us cost advantages over our competition.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Additionally, although modest, our capital expenditure requirements and operating expenses can be temporarily reduced in response to anticipated or actual lower sales in a particular year to maximize cash flow.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Flexible, Lean Enterprise Platform.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;We will continue to utilize lean principles to maximize the flexibility, efficiency and productivity of our manufacturing operations while reducing the associated costs, enabling us to increase distributor and end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;user satisfaction. For example, in an environment where shorter lead times and near
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;perfect order fulfillment are important to our distributors, we believe our lean processes have helped us to improve our shipping performance and build a reputation for providing industry leading shipping performance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Our Growth Opportunities
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Opportunistically Seek New Products and New Markets.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On December 31, 2014 the Company completed its acquisition of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Henderson,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	which gave the Company Henderson&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	full line of product offerings and acce
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ss to its network of dealers.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Previous
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ly, on May&nbsp;6, 2013, the Company acquired substant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ially all of the assets of TrynE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	x, including its full line of product offerings and access to its network of authorized dealers. We expect to continue to consider external growth opportunities within the snow and ice control industry and other equipment or component markets.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We did not complete any material acquisitions during the year ended December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We plan to continue to evaluate other acquisition opportunities within our industry that can help us expand our distribution reach, enhance our technology and as a consequence improve the breadth and depth of our product lines. We also consider diversification opportunities in adjacent markets that complement our business model and could offer us the ability to leverage our core competencies to create stockholder value.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Increase Our Industry Leading Market
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Share.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;We plan to leverage our industry leading position, distribution network and new product innovation capabilities to capture market share in the North American snow and ice control equipment market, focusing our primary efforts on increasing penetration in those North American markets where we believe our overall market share is less than 50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	including
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the heavy duty truck market
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. We also plan to continue growing our presence in the snow and ice control equipment market outside of North America, particularly in Asia and Europe, which we believe could provide significant growth opportunities in the future.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We are party to a financing program in which certain distributors may elect to finance their purchases from us through a third party financing company. We provide the third party financing company recourse against us regarding the collectability of the receivable under the program due to the fact that if the third party financing company is unable to collect from the distributor the amounts due in respect of the product financed, we would be obligated to repurchase any remaining inventory related to the product financed and reimburse any legal fees incurred by the financing company. <FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	upon a combination of patents, trade secrets and trademarks to protect certain of the proprietary aspects of its business and technology. After the date of these financial statements but before the date of this filing,

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Raw Materials
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	During 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	experienced
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	favorable commodity costs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	compared to the slightly
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	un
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	favorable prices paid for commodities in 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Historically
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, we have mitigated, and we currently expect to continue to mitigate, commodity cost increases in part by engaging in proactive vendor negotiations, reviewing alternative sourcing options, substituting materials, engaging in internal cost reduction efforts, and increasing prices on some of our products, all as appropriate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Most of the components of our products are also affected by commodity cost pressures and are commercially available from a number of sources. In 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, we experienced no significant work stoppages because of shortages of raw materials or commodities. The highest raw material and component costs are generally for steel, which we purchase from several suppliers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Other Information
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We were formed as a Delaware corporation in 2004. We maintain a website with the address www.douglasdynamics.com. We are not including the information contained on our website as part of, or incorporating it by reference into, this report. We make available free of charge (other than an investor&#x2019;s own Internet access charges) through our website our Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;K, quarterly reports on Form&nbsp;10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Q and current reports on Form&nbsp;8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;K, and amendments to these reports, as soon as reasonably practicable after we electronically file such material with, or furnish such material to, the Securities and Exchange Commission (&#x201C;SEC&#x201D;).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;For further information regarding our geographic areas see the Summary of Significant Accounting Policies a
</FONT>

<EFX_RISK_FACTORS>
<A NAME="FIS_RISK_FACTORS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item&nbsp;1
</FONT>
<A NAME="PLOW-20151231X10K_HTM_ITEM1A_77145">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	A.&nbsp;&nbsp;Risk Factors
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The Company operates in an environment that involves numerous known and unknown risks and uncertainties. Our business, prospects, financial condition and operating results could be materially adversely affected by any of these risks, as well as other risks not currently known to us or that we currently consider immaterial. The risk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	described below highlight some of the factors that have affected, and in the future could affect our operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our results of operations depend primarily on the level, timing and location of snowfall. As a result, a decline in snowfall levels in multiple regions for an extended time could cause our results of operations to decline and adversely affect our ability to pay dividends.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As a manufacturer of snow and ice control equipment for both light and heavy duty trucks, and related parts and accessories, our sales depend primarily on the level, timing and location of snowfall in the regions in which we offer our products. A low level or lack of snowfall in any given year in any of the snow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;belt regions in North America (primarily the Midwest, East and Northeast regions of the United States as well as all provinces of Canada) will likely cause sales of our products to decline in such year as well as the subsequent year, which in turn may adversely affect our results of operations and ability to pay dividends. See &#x201C;Management&#x2019;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations&#x2014;Seasonality and Year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Year Variability.&#x201D; A sustained period of reduced
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage11"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	snowfall events in one or more of the geographic regions in which we offer our products could cause our results of operations to decline and adversely affect our ability to pay dividends.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;year variability of our business can cause our results of operations and financial condition to be materially different from year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;year; whereas the seasonality of our business can cause our results of operations and financial condition to be materially different from quarter
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;quarter.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Because our business depends on the level, timing and location of snowfall, our results of operations vary from year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year. Additionally, because the annual snow season typically only runs from October&nbsp;1 through March&nbsp;31, our distributors typically purchase our products during the second and third quarters. As a result, we operate in a seasonal business. We not only experience seasonality in our sales, but also experience seasonality in our working capital needs. Consequently, our results of operations and financial condition can vary from year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year, as well as from quarter
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quarter, which could affect our ability to pay dividends. If we are unable to effectively manage the seasonality and year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year variability of our business, our results of operations, financial condition and ability to pay dividends may suffer.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	If economic conditions in the United States continue to remain weak or deteriorate further,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	or if spending by governmental agencies is limited or reduced,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	our results of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	operations, financial condition and ability to pay dividends may be adversely affected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Historically, demand for snow and ice control equipment for light
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and heavy duty
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	trucks has been influenced by general economic conditions in the United States, as well as local economic conditions in the snow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;belt regions in North America. During the last few years, economic conditions througho
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ut the United States have been
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	weak
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and spending by governmental agencies such as Departments of Transportation (&#x201C;DOTs&#x201D;) and municipalities has been constrained
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Although conditions improved from 2011 through 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, they may not become strong in the foreseeable future. Weakened economic conditions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and limited or reduced government spending
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	may cause our end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users to delay purchases of replacement snow and ice control equipment and instead repair their existing equipment, leading to a decrease in our sales of new equipment. Weakened economic conditions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and limited or reduced governmental spending
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	may also cause our end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users to delay their purchases of new light
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and heavy duty
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	trucks. Because our end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users tend to purchase new snow and ice control equipment concurrent with their purchase of new light
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or heavy duty
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	trucks, their delay in purchasing new light
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or heavy duty
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	trucks can also result in the deferral of their purchases of new snow and ice control equipment. The deferral of new equipment purchases during periods of weak economic conditions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or limited or reduced government spending
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	may negatively affect our results of operations, financial condition and ability to pay dividends.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Weakened economic conditions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or limited or reduced government spending
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	may also cause our end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users to consider price more carefully in selecting new snow and ice control equipment. Historically, considerations of quality and service have outweighed considerations of price, but in a weak economy,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or an environment of constrained government spending,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	price may become a more important factor. Any refocus away from quality in favor of cheaper equipment could cause end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users to shift away from our products to less expensive competitor products, or to shift away from our more profitable products to our less profitable products, which in turn would adversely affect our results of operations and our ability to pay dividends.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our failure to maintain good relationships with our distributors, the loss or consolidation of our distributor base or the actions or inactions of our distributors could have an adverse effect on our results of operations and our ability to pay dividends.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We depend on a network of truck equipment distributors to sell, install and service our products. Nearly all of these sales and service relationships are at will, so almost all of our distributors could discontinue the sale and service of our products at any time, and those distributors that primarily sell our products may choose to sell competing products at any time. Further, difficult economic or other circumstances could cause any of our distributors to discontinue their businesses. Moreover, if our distributor base were to consolidate or if any of our distributors were to discontinue their business, competition for the business of fewer distributors would intensify. If we do not maintain good relationships with our distributors, or if we do not provide product offerings and pricing that meet the needs of our distributors, we could lose a substantial amount of our distributor base. A loss of a substantial portion of our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">

<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage12"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#PLOW-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:11.7647058823529%;MARGIN-RIGHT:11.7647058823529%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	distributor base could cause our sales to decline significantly, which would have an adverse effect on our results of operations and ability to pay dividends.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition, our distributors may not provide timely or adequate service to our end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users. If this occurs, our brand identity and reputation may be damaged, which would have an adverse effect on our results of operations and ability to pay dividends.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Lack of available financing options for our end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;users or distributors may adversely affect our sales volumes.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;user base is highly concentrated among professional snowplowers, who comprise over 50% of our end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users, many of whom are individual landscapers who remove snow during the winter and landscape during the rest of the year, rather than large, well
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;capitalized corporations. These end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users often depend upon credit to purchase our products. If credit is unavailable on favorable terms or at all, our end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users may not be able to purchase our products from our distributors, which would in turn reduce sales and adversely affect our results of operations and ability to pay dividends.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition, because our distributors, like our end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users, rely on credit to purchase our products, if our distributors are not able to obtain credit, or access credit on favorable terms, we may experience delays in payment or nonpayment for delivered products. Further, if our distributors are unable to obtain credit or access credit on favorable terms, they could experience financial difficulties or bankruptcy and cease purchases of our products altogether. Thus, if financing is unavailable on favorable terms or at all, our results of operations and ability to pay dividends would be adversely affected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	The price of steel, a commodity necessary to manufacture our products, is highly variable. If the price of steel increases, our gross margins could decline.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Steel is a significant r
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	aw material used to manufacture our products. During 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5, 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, our steel purchases were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	approximately 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	%, 13% and 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	% of our revenue, respectively. The steel industry is highly cyclical in nature, and steel prices have been volatile in recent years and may remain volatile in the future. Steel prices are influenced by numerous factors beyond our control, including general economic conditions domestically and internationally, the availability of raw materials, competition, labor costs, freight and transportation costs, production costs, import duties and other trade restrictions. Steel prices are volatile and may increase as a result of increased demand from the automobile and consumer durable sectors. If the price of steel increases, our variable costs may increase. We may not be able to mitigate these increased costs through the implementation of permanent price increases or temporary invoice surcharges, especially if economic conditions remain weak and our distributors and end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;users become more price sensitive. If we are unable to successfully mitigate such cost increases in the future, our gross margins could decline.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	If petroleum prices increase, our results of operations could be adversely affected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Petroleum prices have fluctuated significantly in recent years. Prices and availability of petroleum products are subject to political, economic and market factors that are outside of our control. Political events in petroleum
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;producing regions as well as hurricanes and other weather
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;related events may cause the price of fuel to increase. If the price of fuel increases, the demand for our products may decline, which would adversely affect our financial condition and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We depend on outside suppliers who may be unable to meet our volume and quality requirements, and we may be unable to obtain alternative sources.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We purchase certain components essential to our snowplows and sand and salt spreaders from outside suppliers, including off
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;shore sources. Most of our key supply arrangements can be discontinued at any time. A supplier may encounter delays in the production and delivery of such products and components or may supply us with products and components that do not meet our quality, quantity or cost requirements. Additionally, a supplier may be forced to discontinue operations. Any discontinuation or interruption in the availability of quality products and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
